RPM Installation in Linux


Installation of a Package 


rpm -ivh pidgin-2.7.9-5.el6.2.i686.rpm
rpm -ivh --nodeps idgin-2.7.9-5.el6.2.i686.rpm

-i : install a package
-v : verbose for a nicer display
-h: print hash marks as the package archive is unpacked.
--nodeps : no dependencies check

Checking lasting installed Packages

rpm -qa --last

Checking particular package installed

rpm -qa | grep pcre

Removing a package without dependencies

 rpm -e pcre-7.8-6.el6.x86_64 --nodeps

Removing a package completely

rpm -e pcre-7.8-6.el6.x86_64

Quering information of a package

rpm -qi vsftpd
